40|$|We {{show that}} {{techniques}} inspired by Kollár and Viehweg's study of weak positivity, combined with vanishing theorems for log-canonical pairs, {{lead to new}} consequences regarding generation and vanishing properties for <b>direct</b> <b>images</b> of pluricanonical bundles. We formulate the strongest such results as Fujita conjecture-type statements, which are then shown to govern a range of fundamental properties of <b>direct</b> <b>images</b> of pluricanonical and pluriadjoint line bundles, like effective vanishing theorems, weak positivity, or generic vanishing. Comment: 18 pages; minor corrections, final version to appear in AN...|$|R
