50|$|The <b>direct</b> <b>image</b> of a {{coherent}} sheaf is often not coherent. For example, for a field k, let X be the affine line over k, and consider the morphism f: X → Spec(k); then the <b>direct</b> <b>image</b> f*OX is the sheaf on Spec(k) associated to the polynomial ring kx, which is not coherent because kx has infinite dimension as a k-vector space. On the other hand, the <b>direct</b> <b>image</b> of {{a coherent}} sheaf under a proper morphism is coherent, by results of Grauert and Grothendieck.|$|E
